==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: firstborn
<hw>first"born`</hw> <pr>(f⟦etil⟧rst"b⟦ocir⟧rn`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The first child born to a parent; <as>as, his <ex>firstborn</ex>
was showered with gifts from relatives</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eldest.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firstborn</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Firstborn
<hw>First"born`</hw> <pr>(f⟦etil⟧rst"b⟦ocir⟧rn`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>First brought forth; first in the order of birth; eldest; hence,
most excellent; most distinguished or exalted; <as>as, the
<ex>firstborn</ex> child</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eldest.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>first-class</ent>⟦br⟧
